      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay but u keep saying \"extreme nationalism\" is the bad part. but isn't that just a way to dismiss the actual benefits? like, if a country doesn't have a strong national identity and clear borders, doesn't it just fall apart into chaos? it feels like you're basically saying any real sense of national unity is a risk, which seems pretty biased towards a globalist view. shouldn't a stable society actually rely on these things to function?",
